{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17630985","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17630985"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T17:21:18+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T17:21:18+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17342"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17342","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17342"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.04,0.04,0.29,0.21,0.42]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10032"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78691"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10032","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10032"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17342"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"64034"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4926"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"5586"},{"type":"tags","id":"6742"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"23487"},{"type":"contributions","id":"23491"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78691","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/78691"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following arteries provides the main blood supply to the lateral wall of the nasal cavity?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Greater palatine artery","Superior labial artery","Sphenopalatine artery","Posterior ethmoidal artery","Anterior ethmoidal artery"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Esphenopalatine artery\u003C/strong\u003E provides the main blood supply to the lateral wall of the nasal cavity. It enters through the sphenopalatine foramen and is a terminal branch of the maxillary artery.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe other arteries have different distributions:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eanterior ethmoidal artery\u003C/strong\u003E supplies the anterior superior portion of the nasal cavity and anterior septum\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Egreater palatine artery\u003C/strong\u003E supplies the inferior portion of the lateral wall and floor of the nasal cavity\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Esuperior labial artery\u003C/strong\u003E supplies the nasal vestibule and anterior portion of the nasal septum (Kiesselbach\u0027s area)\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eposterior ethmoidal artery\u003C/strong\u003E supplies a small portion of the superior nasal cavity and posterior septum\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EUnderstanding this vascular anatomy is important for managing epistaxis, as different bleeding locations may require different approaches to achieve haemostasis.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The sphenopalatine artery is the terminal branch of the maxillary artery and provides the main blood supply to the lateral wall of the nasal cavity.","The anterior and posterior ethmoidal arteries arise from the ophthalmic artery and supply the superior portion of the nasal cavity.","The greater palatine artery supplies the inferior portion of the nasal cavity and hard palate."],"references":["Netter FH. Netter Atlas of Human Anatomy: A Regional Approach with Latin Terminology. Eighth edition. Elsevier; 2022.","Moore KL, Dalley AF, Agur A. Clinically Oriented Anatomy. 8th ed. Lippincott Williams and Wilkins; 2017."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"64034"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"ques